<table class="contentpaneopen">



<tr>
<td valign="top">
<p><img height="300" width="237" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-health-safety.jpg" alt="eden-health-safety" style="float: right;" />COSHH is the Care of Substances Hazardous to Health and encompasses any substances that you use or store, within your business, that may present a risk to health. Typical things to consider are cleaning products such as bleach, sanitary chemicals and dishwasher tablets but what you may not have considered are substances such as washing up liquid and polishes and the like.</p>
<p>All of these substances need to be assessed in terms or their risk, for instance, do you have to use a particular chemical? or could you use one with less potential harmful effects? How do you store the chemicals? Who is responsible for these substances in your organisation?</p>
<p>These are all things you need to identify, consider and record. Let Eden help you to meet your health and safety obligations</p></td>
</tr>

